EEX Signs Extension With Germany to Hold 2012 Emissions Auction

-- B y   L a r s   P a u l s s o n
-- 
2011-04-18T10:31:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/eex-signs-extension-with-germany-to-hold-2012-emissions-auction.html
European Energy Exchange AG,
continental  Europe ’s biggest energy trading platform, will hold
 Germany ’s primary emissions auctions in 2012 after extending an
accord with the Federal Ministry of Environment.  The extension, signed on April 15, covers European Union
emission allowances for spot and futures trading, the Leipzig,
Germany-based bourse said today in an e-mailed statement.  EEX has held the German auction since January 2010 for spot
and futures contracts and about 40 million allowances have been
sold for the government.  To contact the reporters responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  